             <div class="art-article">
              <h1 style="text-align: center;">
               Village Family Psychiatry, PLLC
              </h1>
              <!-- (draft) -->
              <h3 style="text-align: center;">
               Psychiatric and Psychological Services In An Integrated and Collaborative Setting
              </h3>
              <p>
               Village Family Psychiatry, PLLC provides multi-disciplinary psychiatric and psychological services that integrates both the neurobiologic and psychosocial/behavioral components of treatment.  We treat a broad range of psychiatric disorders that includes DEPRESSIVE AND ANXIETY DISORDERS, MOOD DISORDERS, ATTENTION DEFICIT HYPERACTIVITY DISORDERS, PSYCHOTIC DISORDERS, SITUATIONAL AND ADJUSTMENT DISORDERS, AND A BROAD RANGE OF CHILD AND ADOLESCENT DISORDERS.  This includes various developmental disorders such as Autism, Asperger’s Disorder, Pervasive Developmental Disorders, Tic Disorders, Eating Disorders and Behavioral and Conduct Disorders along with diagnosis and management of  learning problems.  Low grade substance abuse issues can be addressed, but we do not provide more comprehensive addiction services.
              </p>
              <p>
               Each patient receives a thorough assessment either starting with a trained non-physician therapist or one of our psychiatrists.  Our services include both medical management of psychiatric issues with our physicians and therapeutic services provided by both Master’s Level Clinicians as well as Doctorate Level Psychologists. Our psychologists also provide various psychological, educational and neuropsychological testing.  With 2 Doubly Board Certified Child and Adolescent and General Psychiatrists on our staff, we are in a unique position of being able to provide integrated services to our patients where communication between collaborating clinicians is a simple walk down the hall.
              </p>
              <p>
               We accept a broad range of Insurance plans and work to insure that our clients receive maximum benefit from the insurance coverage that they hold.  We have an excellent administrative and support staff that works to make your experience of needing help as simple and comfortable as possible.  We answer telephone calls in real time with real people and this makes access during office hours very easy.  They are available to field questions and concerns prior to your being registered as a patient and then afterward as issues and difficulties arise.
              </p>
              <p>
               We take pride in providing an office ambiance that is comfortable and caring.  Getting help for emotional issues can be difficult and taxing and we strive to provide an overall environment that is respectful of problems, careful to assure privacy, and yet humane and “people friendly” so you will feel positive about getting help.
              </p>
             </div>
